title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message:
Hi.

Got this board yesterday.
When I press powerbutton the fan spins for 5 sec then it dies.
For some strange reason I decided to keep holding down the powerbutton longer and after 10 sec I heard noice from the dvd drive and after that a normal DONG.
It booted normal and everything seems to work.

I have tried another keyboard with same results.

What is causing this problem?

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message: R7051, R7052, R7021 and R7022 is all good

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message: What is PPBUS voltage? Does it charge?

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message:
PPBUS_G3H is 12.63v
PP3V42_G3H is 3.42v
PP3V3_S5 is 3.3v

they are all stable and doesn't change.
Battery is charging.

Board Looks nice

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message: Try and run ASD to check for errors

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message:
Ok

Current (IPOR) --Battery-BMON Eng (test 1) - Sensor Reads Within Operating Range

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message: Check sense resistors and traces again, this is a current sense issue in R7050/51/52 circuit. Corroded trace or resistor, measure resistance between pins 17 and 18.

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message:
yes
R7050 looks a bit strange. the solder is dark  grey

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message: no contact from R7051 to R7050

title: [SOLVED]820-2879 strange power on
message:
replaced R7050 and ran a jumper from R7051 and now the error error in ASD is gone and everything seems to work.

Thanks alot for your help
